<TABLE ALIGN=LEFT BORDER="3" CELLPADDING="3" CELLSPACING="3">
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="buttons/theatrebtsm.gif" ALT="Theatre" HEIGHT=47 WIDTH=58 BORDER=0></TD></TABLE>
<BR><BR><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=6> Augusta Area Theatre</FONT>

<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=6><B>DECEMBER</B></FONT></CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<H3>December 6, 7, 8, 13, 14</H3>
<UL><FONT SIZE=4>
<LI><B>Harvey.</B><BR>
Aiken Community Playhouse Youth Wing.  This Pulitzer Prize play  written by Mary Chase about gentle Elwood P. Dowd and  his friend Harvey (who happens to be a Pooka) has been charming audiences since it premiered in 1944.  It will make you believe in Pook
as!  Directed by Angie Fitzgerald.  Sunday Matinee December 8 at 3:00 pm
</UL></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=6><B>JANUARY</B></FONT></CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<H3>January 31</H3>
<UL><FONT SIZE=4>
<LI><B>The Winter's Tale and  Our Town.  (706) 793-8552</B><BR>
Fort Gordon Dinner Theater.  Come out and enjoy the Classic Theater Alliance's production of The Winter's Tale and  Our Town.
</UL></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=6><B>FEBRUARY</B></FONT></CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<H3>February 1 - 15</H3>
<UL><FONT SIZE=4>
<LI><B>The Winter's Tale and  Our Town.  (706) 793-8552</B><BR>
Fort Gordon Dinner Theater.  Come out and enjoy the Classic Theater Alliance's production of The Winter's Tale and  Our Town.
</UL></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE>
<H3>February 2</H3>
<UL><FONT SIZE=4>
<LI><A HREF="http://sdirect.com/theatre/pb"><B>The Pied Piper of Hamelin</A>  (706) 826-4707</B><BR>
Augusta Players.  Lamar Elementary School.  3:00 pm.  The Augusta Players Imagine That! Theater will present this adaptation of Robert Browning's classic tale tells of a miserly town council which refuses to pay the piper after his enchanting music rids t
he town of its rats.  So the Piper plays again, this time leading the town's children away into the mountains until town leaders repent and honor their bargain.
</UL></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE>
<H3>February 4, 5, 6, 7, & 9</H3>
<UL><FONT SIZE=4>
<LI><B>The Enchanted Well  (706) 731-0054</B><BR>
Storyland Theater.  Written by Richard Davis Jr.  February 4 - 6 at 9:30 am, 10:45am and 12:15 pm.  February 9 at 3:00 pm.  Reservations required for weekday school performances.  Individual performances $3 per student.  No reservations required or Sunday
 Family Matinees.
</UL></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE>
<H3>February 21 -23</H3>
<UL><FONT SIZE=4>
<LI><A HREF="http://sdirect.com/theatre"><B>The Diary of Anne Frank</A>  (706) 826-4707</B><BR>
Augusta Players.  Tubman Middle School.  Performances February 21 and 22 at 8:00 pm and February 23 at 3:00pm.  The Augusta Players Youth Theater will present one of the finest dramas of our time.  The Diary of Anne Frank  was the winner of virtually ever
y coveted prize for theater.  This wonderfully crafted theatrical experience is based on the real life legacy left to us by a spirited, straightforward Jewish girl whose diary tells of the horror and difficult times she and a small group endured while hid
ing from the Nazis in Amsterdam.  Experience the fears, the anguish, and the sometimes flaring humor ofthis outstanding piece of theater.
</UL></FONT>

<HR NOSHADE>
