<BR>
<Font Size=5>Searching the World Wide Web<P><FONT SIZE=3>You'll find 
browsing through the World Wide Web's Search Engines is easy here at 
Einstein's Chalkboard.  Just so you don't lose us, any link you chose 
from this page will bring up a new browser window so if you end up in the 
Australian Outback or the Library of Congress, we'll be right behind!</Font>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=4>
<A HREF="http://altavista.digital.com/">AltaVista</A>  AltaVista gives you access to the largest Web index: 30 million pages found on 225,000 servers, and three million articles from 14,000 Usenet news groups. It is accessed over 12 million times per day.


 
<P>
 You may Search AltaVista here<BR>
<P>
<IMG SRC= Altavista.gif><P>
<FORM method=GET action="http://altavista.digital.com/cgi-bin/query" 
target=guide> <INPUT TYPE=hidden NAME=pg VALUE=q>
<B>Search <SELECT NAME=what>
<OPTION VALUE=web SELECTED>the Web
<OPTION VALUE=news>Usenet
</SELECT>
and Display the Results <SELECT NAME=fmt>
<OPTION VALUE="" SELECTED>in Standard Form
<OPTION VALUE=c>in Compact Form
<OPTION VALUE=d>in Detailed Form
</SELECT></B><BR>
<INPUT NAME=q size=55 maxlength=200 VALUE="">
<INPUT TYPE=submit VALUE=Submit>
</FORM>
<BR>
<P>
<HR>
<P> 
<A HREF="http://guide.infoseek.com/Home?pg=Home.html&sv=N1" 
target=guide>InfoSeek</A>
    Infoseek's free Internet search services, Net Search and Guide are the most
popular ones on the Net today, receiving over 5 million information requests per day from over 1 million unique Internet users worldwide
<p>
<a href="http://www.excite.com/" target=guide>excite NetSearch</A> excite's 
NetSearch 
contains lots of information for you to search over -- at present, 11.5 million Web pages and two weeks of Usenet news articles and classified ads. 
<p>
<HR>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.lycos.com/" target=guide>Lycos</A>,<A 
HREF="http://www.pointcom.com/" target=guide> Point</A>, and <A 
HREF="http://a2z.lycos.com/" target=guide>A2Z</A> are a trio of stars in the 
same 
information universe, as Carl Sagan might say. Lycos provides searches of the entire Internet, Point offers reviews and ratings of the top 5% of all Internet sites, and A2Z is a new service offering a categorized directory of the Net's most often hyperlin


ked sites. All three sites are operated by Lycos, Incorporated.
<P>
<img src=Lycos3.gif><BR>
