<p>
<Font Size=5> More Searchable Databases</FONT>
<P>
<Font Size=4>
<P>
<a href="http://www.einet.net/galaxy.html" target=guide>EINet Galaxy</A>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<a href="http://www.dejanews.com/" target=guide>DejaNews</A> Search a vast 
archive of Usenet news postings by keyword, author, and date. <P>
You may Search DejaNews here<BR>
<P>
<FORM ACTION="http://search.dejanews.com/dnquery.xp" METHOD=post 
target=guide> <A HREF="http://www.dejanews.com/">
<IMG SRC="http://www.dejanews.com/gifs/dnbanner2small.gif"
ALT=" [ Deja News ] " ALIGN=left></A>
<STRONG>Search Usenet For:</STRONG>
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="query" SIZE="30">
<INPUT TYPE="submit" VALUE="Find">
<BR>Select documents matching
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="defaultOp" Value="AND" CHECKED>all
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="defaultOp" Value="OR">any
keywords.
<BR>Display histlist in
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="format" Value="terse" CHECKED>concise
<INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="format" Value="verbose">detailed
format.
</FORM>
<BR>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<a href="http://www.albany.net/allinone/" target=guide>ALL-IN-ONE Search 
Page</A>
This page is a compilation of various forms-based search tools found on the Internet. They have been combined here to form a consistent interface and convenient ALL-IN-ONE search point.
<P>
<a href="http://wwww.cs.colorado.edu/wwww/" target=guide>WWWW - WORLD WIDE 
WEB WORM</a> Serving 3,000,000 URL's to 2,000,000 folks/month.
<P>
<a href="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/DataSources/bySubject/Overview.html" 
target=guide>World Wide Web Virtual Library</a> A Virtual libray with links 
to  topics by subject
<P>
<a href="http://www.nosc.mil/planet_earth/info.html" target=guide>Planet 
Earth Home Page</A> A World Wide Web Virtual Library <P>
<a href="http://lcweb.loc.gov/global/metaindex.html" target=guide>
WWW Meta Indexes and Search Tools</A> A list of subject indexes from the Library of Congress
<P>
<a href="http://lcweb.loc.gov/global/subject.html" target=guide>Library of 
Congress 
Subject Guide</A> A Library of Congress Internet Resource Page. Information Links by subject
<P>
<a href="http://www.el.com/" target=guide>The Web's Essential Links</A> A 
good 
starting place for finding information on the web. Links to references like dictionaries, TV guides and other search tools
<P>
<a href="http://www.isleuth.com/" target=guide>
Internet Sleuth</A> Choose from over 1500 Searchable Databases
<P>
<A HREF="http://thelist.com/" target=guide>The List (Internet Service 
Providers)</A> 
A database of more than 2,950 internet service providers and growing. Search by location, area code or name.
<P> 
<a href="http://scuish.scu.edu/SCU/Programs/Diversity/esources.html" 
target=guide>Electronic Resources on Diversity</A> African American, Asian 
American, 
European American, Latino/as, Middle Eastern American and Native American pages.
<P>
<a 
href="http://info.umd.edu:86/Educational_Resources/AcademicResourcesByTopic/WomensStudies/" target=guide>InforM Womens Studies Database</A> The most comprehensive site for academic women's studies resources, including syllabi, papers, film reviews, biblio


graphies, links to women's studies departments, the best compilation of woman gender feminist male studies listservs. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://okra.ucr.edu/okra/info.html">OKRA</A> Look for individual email addresses. "OKRA information is gathered from many different sources. . . All we do is take information that is already publicly available and put it into a convenient interfa


ce. "
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.iaf.net/" target=guide>Internet Address Finder</A> IAF 
claims it 
has more than 3.5 million names on tap. Just enter a piece of a name and a list of matching e-mail addresses pop up. Likewise, the database can handle a reverse search, which spits out a name when given an address.
<P> 
<A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/search/people/" target=guide> Yahoo's People 
Search</A> Telephone/address - e-mail addresses - homepages <p>
<A HREF="http://www.neosoft.com/internet/paml/byname.html#G" target=guide>
Publicly Accessible Mailing Lists - Index by Name</A> Search by name, keyword for basic information about listservs
  address, owner, subscription information.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.switchboard.com/" target=guide>Switchboard</A> Find 
people or 
businesses. Registered users can modify their own records and get more information on people like email addresses.
<P>
<a href="http://auth.pathfinder.com/info/misc/isocountry.html" target=guide>
ISO Country Codes</STRONG></A> Lists the International Standards Organization's two-letter country codes for Internet addresses -- 238 so far. These are the two character codes found at the end of Internet addresses.
<P>
<a href="http://www.iTools.com/" target=guide>iTools! Find it, Research it, 
Promote it</A>
Find what you need fast using the top Internet search tools.  Look up phone numbers, addresses, stock quotes,  package tracking, and more in this indispensable tool. Let the world know about your web site with the most complete set of sites to announce yo


ur site. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://www2.islandnet.com/~luree/fanmail.html" 
target=guide>Celebrity Addresses</A> Email addresses and homepages. Some of the pages are maintained by the celebrity but most are fan pages. The "inhuman" category takes you to a page of cartoon links.
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Listserv</FONT><FONT SIZE=4> (email discussion groups)
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.nova.edu/Inter-Links/cgi-bin/lists" target=guide>
Search List of Discussion Groups</A>
The database of lists employed here comes from the list of Bitnet and Internet Interest Groups maintained at Dartmouth College. There are currently more than 5900 entries.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.tile.net/tile/listserv/index.html" target=guide>
Tile.Net/Lists</A> Browse for listserv descriptions by name, subject, country of origin, sponsoring organization.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
