<HTML>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" BACKGROUND="omnipapr.gif" TEXT="#000000" LINK="CBOOO5" VLINK="000000" ALINK="000000">


<HEAD><TITLE>OmniQuest Services</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>


<CENTER>
<IMG ALT="OmniQuest Services" SRC="omninu.gif"><BR>
P.O. Box 14426, Augusta, Georgia  30919<BR>Ph. (706) 731-9272  Fax (706) 
737-4886</FONT><BR><A HREF="mailto:omniquest@sdirect.com">email: 
omniquest@sdirect.com</A><BR> 
<P>



<FONT SIZE=6><B>Remote Backup Service </B>(R.B.S.)</FONT><BR><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<TABLE BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD><IMG ALT="Did You Know??" SRC="diduknow.gif"></TD>
<TD>Only a small percentage of business computers have an easy way to make regular backups.  Thousands of small businesses that do not perform regular backups lose hundreds of thousands of dollars in data annually to one of the following:<BR><B>Fire - Theft - Equipment Failure - Lightning - Power Surges - Human Error</TD></TABLE>
<P>
<B>When disaster strikes destroying computers and backups, backups not stored off site cause many businesses to go broke.</B> <P>
A Study by the University of Texas disclosed <B>"that nearly half the companies that lose their data never re-open.</B>  
The same study concludes that <B>90% of these data losses occur, "due to power failures, loose cables, hardware, software or human error."</B><P>
<B>Within eight days</B> of a continuing outage, <B>a business loses 2-3% of their gross sales.</B>
<HR NOSHADE>

<FONT SIZE=4><B>"A business experiencing a loss of their computers for greater than 10 days will never fully recover.  Half of these will go out of business within 5 years."</B></FONT><HR NOSHADE><P>
<TABLE BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD><IMG ALT="What Can A Crash Cost You??" SRC="whatcost.gif"></TD>
<TD>A disaster recovery study from the University of Texas reports that if a company loses 20 megabytes of sales data and has to hire temporary employees to quickly re-input the lost data, the replacement would take approximately 19 days and $17,000.00<BR


><B>Labor is expensive</B></TD></TABLE>

<HR NOSHADE>
<FONT SIZE=4><CENTER><B>How long would it take and how much would it cost your company?</B></CENTER></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE> 
<P>

<IMG ALT="What Do You Spend On Backups??" SRC="whatspend.gif">
<UL><LI>You pay your employee $7.50/Hr.<BR><LI>It takes 1 hour each day for the incremental backup and verify.  (Full backups take much longer.)<BR><LI>$7.50 x 260 days=$1950.00 per year.</UL>
This analysis only includes labor and time cost.  No cost of equipment, repairs, and supplies or the availablility of the computer during backup time.
<HR NOSHADE>
<FONT COLOR="#129B43" SIZE=4><CENTER><B>We WILL save you money and secure your valuable computer data!</B></CENTER></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE>

<P>
<IMG ALT="What Do You Need??" SRC="whatneed.gif">
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="check.gif"></TD>
<TD>You need a telephone line - non dedicated</TD>
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="check.gif"></TD>
<TD>You need a high speed modem</TD> <TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="check.gif"></TD>
<TD>You need our Remote Backup scheduling software on your computer or network.</TD></TABLE></CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<FONT SIZE=4><CENTER><B>AND THAT'S ALL YOU'LL NEED!!</B></CENTER></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE>
<IMG ALT="How It Works..." SRC="howworks.gif"><BR>
<UL><LI>At a pre-set time, your computer wakes up, compresses your data into an encrypted password protected format.<BR><LI>Then via modem, your system calls our archival system.<BR><LI>The computers identify each other, then your computer transmits it's 


backup data.<BR><LI>In the morning, your data is transferred to tape and placed in our fire proof vault.</UL>

<HR NOSHADE>
<FONT SIZE=4><CENTER><B>Stored Safe, Secure and Off-site</B></CENTER></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
<TABLE BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD><IMG ALT="Why Omniquest Services??" SRC="whyomni.gif"></TD>
<TD>At Omniquest Services, you will quickly realize that we are not your average computer center.  Our motto is <B>"Customer Satisfaction First"</B>.  The emphasis of our business is on service. not trying to sell you something you do not need or want.</T


D></TABLE><BR>
We offer a full line of on-site help and service to our customers whether corporate or individual.  We specialize in remote backups, data recovery, hard drive diagnostics, computer repairs, computer upgrades, and internet training.  <B>We want you to get 


the most out of the equipment that you already own.</B>

<HR NOSHADE>
<FONT SIZE=4><CENTER><B>When your computer company's <I>helpline</I> is not working for you, give us a call and step up to the service you deserve.</B></CENTER></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE> 
<P>

</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="5"><TD>Welcome Visitor</TD><TD 
ALIGN="CENTER"><B>1,111</B></TD></TABLE>
