Leonardo da Vinci Museum</A> The original "Renaissance Man", Leonardo da Vinci was a great painter, designer, scientist, futurist
and thinker. His works are even more popular now than they were in his day.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.vol.it/mirror/wwWright/">The wwWright Site</A>
 contains four collections of photographs of Frank Lloyd Wright's architecture built in Minnesota and Racine, Wisconsin.
<P>
<A HREF="http://rubens.anu.edu.au/">ArtServe</A> Art & Architecture from The Australian National University. This server offers access to around 16,000 images (NOT available elsewhere) all concerned in some way with the history of art and architecture.
<p>
<a href="http://sunsite.unc.edu/louvre/">WebMuseum</A>  contains Medieval art, general exhibitions including the Famous Painting Collections and more
<P>
<A href=" http://www.art.uiuc.edu/kam/.">The Krannert Art Museum</A>    at the University of Illinois  features a selection of hypermedia displays including "Science in the Art Museum" and the "Virtual Gallery" tour. As well as an Education Resource Cente

r.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.msstate.edu/Fineart_Online/art-resources/">  Directory of Art Related Web Resources</A> concerning art and in the possible relationships between art and technology. This indexes well over 1000 art resources
