0))'>
<META http-equiv="PICS-Label" 
content='(PICS-1.0 "http://www.classify.org/safesurf/" l gen t for
"http://http://www.sdirect.com/einstein/" r (SS~~000 1 SS~~100 1))'>
<meta name="rating" content="safe for kids">
<BODY>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<CENTER>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="astronomy.gif"><P>
<FONT SIZE=4>
/ <A HREF="art.html"> Art</A> / <A HREF="astronomy.html"> Astronomy  &AMP Space</A> / <A HREF="biology.html"> Biology</A> / <A HREF="chemistry.html"> Chemistry</A> / <A HREF="computers.html"> Computers</A> / <A HREF="dictionary.html"> Dictonaries &amp References</A> / <A HREF="environment.html"> Environment</A> / <A HREF="geography.html"> Geography</A> / <A HREF="geology.html"> Geology</A> / <A HREF="government.html"> Government</A> / <A HREF="history.html"> History</A>  / <A HREF="internet.html"> Internet Search</A> / <A HREF="libraries.html"> Libraries</A> / <A HREF="literature.html"> Literature</A>  / <A HREF="math.html"> Math</A> / <A HREF="museums.html"> Museums</A> / <A HREF="music.html"> Music</A>  / <A HREF="news.html"> News &amp Current events</A
>  / <A HREF="perform.html"> Performing Arts</A> / <A HREF="physics.html"> Physics</A> / <A HREF="weather.html">  Weather</A> /
</CENTER>
<font size=4>
<BR>
<P>

<p>
<A href="http://www.eia.brad.ac.uk/btl/">Stars and Galaxies</A> This database is brought to you by the department of Industrial Technology at the University of Bradford, and  gives a comprehensive multimedia guide to Stars and Galaxies. All the text, audi

o and
pictures are taken from the PC CDROM Earth and Universe from BTL Publishing Limited.
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.fourmilab.ch/earthview/vplanet.html">Earth Viewer</A> You can view either a map of the Earth showing the day and night regions at this moment, or view the Earth from the Sun, the Moon, the night side of the Earth.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.fourmilab.ch/solar/solar.html">Solar System Live</A> The interactive Orrery of the Web. You can view the entire Solar
System, or just the inner planets (through the orbit of Mars). Controls allow you to set time and date, viewpoint, observing location, orbital elements to track an asteroid or comet, and a variety of other parameters. 
<P>
<A href="http://www.geo.mtu.edu/weather/aurora/">The Aurora Page</A>
Information, links and images about the "Northern Lights".
<p>
<a href="http://planetary.org/TPS/">The Planetary Society</a> Promotes space exploration and education
<P>
<A href="http://www.pa.msu.edu:80/abrams/">The Talbert and Leota Abrams Planetarium</A> An astronomy and space science
education resource center.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.kalmbach.com/astro/astronomy.html">Astronomy Magazine</A> The world's largest English-language
magazine for astronomy hobbyists. Produced by Kalmbach Publishing
Co., it is read by over 300,000 persons each month.

<p>
<A HREF="http://tycho.usno.navy.mil/srss.html">U.S. Naval Observatory time calculator</A> You can calculate the sunrise, sunset, twilight, moonrise, moonset and phase times for U.S. locations
<P>
<A HREF="http:// pds.jpl.nasa.gov/planets.>Welcome to the Planets</A> This is a collection of many of the best images from NASA's planetary exploration program. The collection has been extracted from the interactive program "Welcome to the Planets" which 

was distributed on the Planetary Data System Educational CD-ROM Version 1.5 in December 1995. 

<p>
<A HREF="http://bang.lanl.gov/solarsys/">Views of the Solar System</A> An educational tour of the solar system. It containsimages and information about the Sun, planets, moons, asteroids, comets and meteoroids found
within the solar system. It contains over 220 pages of information, over 950 high-resolution images and animations, and over 880 megabytes of data. 
 <P>
<a href="http://www.stsci.edu/public.html">Hubble Space Telescope</A> Fantastic Images, movies, animations and more.
<p>
<a href="http://seds.lpl.arizona.edu/messier/Messier.html">
The Messier Catalog</A>1782 Charles Messier, a French astronomer (b. 1730 d. 1817),   During the years from 1758 to compiled a list of
approximately 100 diffuse objects that were difficult to
distinguish from comets through the telescopes of the day.And became known for, the Messier Catalog, a collection of the most beautiful objects in the sky including nebulae, star clusters, and galaxies. 
<p>
<a href="http://seds.lpl.arizona.edu/billa/twn/">The Web Nebulae</A>
 Beautiful images of the Nabulae
<P>
<a href="http://bang.lanl.gov/solarsys/"> Views Of The Solar System</a> Images and information about the Sun, planets, moons, asteroids and comets, and the history of space exploration. 
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.astro.wisc.edu/~dolan/constellations/"> The Constellations and their Stars</A>
<p>
<A href="http://www.seds.org/billa/tnp/">The Nine Planet</a> A Multimedia Tour of the Solar System byBillArnett.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/basics/">The Basics of Space Flight</A> Understanding the general concepts associated with space flight in general and deep space missions in particular. 
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.hq.nasa.gov/office/mtpe/"> NASA'S Mission to Planet Earth</a> MTPE is studying how our global environment is changing. Using the unique perspective available from space.
<P>
<a href="http://seds.lpl.arizona.edu/">Students for the Exploration and Development of Space(SEDS)</a> SEDS is an independent,student-based organization which promotes the exploration and development of space. 
<p>
<A href="http://cmex-www.arc.nasa.gov/">The Center for Mars Exploration</A> The Center for Mars Exploration (CMEX) WWW server -many new features including historical references to Mars, previous Mars mission information, tools to analyze Mars, current Mar

s news, and much more. 
<p>
<A HREF="http://newproducts.jpl.nasa.gov/comet/">Comet Hale-Bopp</A> On July 23, 1995, an unusually bright comet outside of Jupiter's orbit was discovered independently by Alan Hale, New Mexico and Thomas Bopp, Arizona. The new comet, designated C/1995 O1

, is the farthest comet ever discovered by amateurs and appeared 1000 times brighter
than Comet Halley did at the same distance.
<P>
<A href="http://www.ksc.nasa.gov/facts/faq12.html">
How to become an astronaut</A> Requirements for the NASA astronaut program.  
<p>
<A HREF="http://stdatu.stsci.edu/dss/">Digitized Palomar Sky Survey</A>  A searchable archive of the premier photographic atlas of the cosmos.
<P>
<A href="http://newproducts.jpl.nasa.gov/calendar/calendar.html">
The Space Calendar</A> The Space Calendar covers space-related activities and anniversaries for the coming year. Included
are over 300 links to other home pages for more information.
<p>
<A href="http://www.nas.nasa.gov/NAS/SpaceSettlement/">Orbital Space Settlements</A> "In the long term, the purposes of [NASA's Human Exploration and Development of Space] Enterprise are to ... enable the eventual establishment of permanent, self-sufficie

nt settlements in space." 


<p>
<A HREF="http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/sircxsar/">Space radar images of Earth</A> Spaceborne Imaging Radar-C/X-Band Synthetic Aperture Radar (SIR-C/X-SAR) is a joint U.S.-German-Italian project that uses a highly sophisticated imaging radar to capture images of

 Earth that are useful to scientists across a great range of disciplines. 
</FONT>
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.speakeasy.org/~chris/pom/">Phase of the Moon</A>  The current phase of the moon.
<P>
<a href="http://www.nasa.gov/">
The National Aeronautics and Space Administration</a> The NASA homepage
<p>
<A HREF="http://hou.lbl.gov/">Hands-On Universe</A> An education program sponsored by the National Science Foundation and the Department of Energy that helps high school students perform genuine astronomical research in their classrooms.
<P>
<A href="http://sln.fi.edu/tfi/hotlists/space.html">Space Science Hotlist</A> This site has links to space related references,as well as science and teacher references.
</BLOCKQUOTE> 
<BR>
<P>
