<meta name="rating" content="safe for kids">
<body>
<CENTER>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="geology.gif"><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=4>
/ <A HREF="art.html"> Art</A> / <A HREF="astronomy.html"> Astronomy  &AMP Space</A> / <A HREF="biology.html"> Biology</A> / <A HREF="chemistry.html"> Chemistry</A> / <A HREF="computers.html"> Computers</A> / <A HREF="dictionary.html"> Dictonaries &amp References</A> / <A HREF="environment.html"> Environment</A> / <A HREF="geography.html"> Geography</A> / <A HREF="geology.html"> Geology</A> / <A HREF="government.html"> Government</A> / <A HREF="history.html"> History</A>  / <A HREF="internet.html"> Internet Search</A> / <A HREF="libraries.html"> Libraries</A> / <A HREF="literature.html"> Literature</A>  / <A HREF="math.html"> Math</A> / <A HREF="museums.html"> Museums</A> / <A HREF="music.html"> Music</A>  / <A HREF="news.html"> News &amp Current events</A
>  / <A HREF="perform.html"> Performing Arts</A> / <A HREF="physics.html"> Physics</A> / <A HREF="weather.html">  Weather</A> /
</CENTER>
<BR>

<P>
<A HREF="http://walrus.wr.usgs.gov/docs/ask-a-ge.html">
Ask A Geologist</A> US Geological Survey Western Region Marine and Coastal Surveys.
<p>
<A href="http://quake.wr.usgs.gov/">Earthquake Information from the USGS</A> From the United States Geological Survey, Geologic Division. 
<P>
<A href="http://www.gps.caltech.edu/~polet/recofd.html">Earthquake of the Day</A> From the  CalTech Seismological Laboratory 
<p>
<A Href="http://www.soest.hawaii.edu:80/hvo/">USGS Hawaiian Volcano Observatory</A> Volcano Watch. A weekly newsletter for the general public published by the US Geological Survey's Hawaiian Volcano
Observatory (HVO).
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.geo.mtu.edu/volcanoes/">MTV Volcanos Page</A> Michigan Technological UniversityVolcanoes Page Sponsored by the Keweenaw Volcano Observatory. Information about volcanoes,current global volcanic activity, research in remote sensing of vo

lcanoes and their eruptive products, hazard mitigation, "Decade Volcanoes", links to government agenciesm and research institutions, and even some volcano humor. 
<P>
<A href="http://sedwww.cr.usgs.gov:8080/radon/">USGS Radon Information</A> Information from previously published USGS reports on radon and its sources in the geologic environment is available here. 
<p>
<A HREF="http://walrus.wr.usgs.gov/docs/margeol.html">Marine Geology</A> Research beneath the sea
<p>
<A href="http://galaxy.einet.net/images/gems/gems-icons.html">Smithsonian Gem & Mineral Collection</A> Images from the gem and mineral collection of the Smithsonian's National Museum of Natural History. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://helios.cr.usgs.gov/gips/aii-home.htm">Understanding Our Planet Through Chemistry</A> This U.S.Geological Survey site shows how chemists and geologists use analytical chemistry to: determine the age of the Earth; show that an extraterrestri

al body collided with the Earth; predict volcanic eruptions; observe
atmospheric change over millions of years; and document damage by acid rain and pollution of the Earth's surface.. Compiled byJoseph E. Taggart, Jr.

<P>
<A HREF="http://info.er.usgs.gov/">The U.S. Geological Survey home page</A> Contains a wealth of information on geology, the environment, terrain, maps, earth sciences, etc.
<p>
<A HREF="http://quake.wr.usgs.gov/QUAKES/WEEKREPS/weekly.html">U.S.G.S. Weekly Seismicity Reports</A> The weekly reports contain detailed information on earthquakes in Northern California and other
information on larger earthquakes in the US and around the World. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://volcano.und.nodak.edu">Volcano World</a> Supported by NASA's Program: Public Use of Earth and Space Science Data Over the Internet
<P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

