<P>
<A HREF="http://www.house.gov/"> U.S. House of Representatives Home Page</A> The U.S. House of Representatives' World Wide Web service provides public access to legislative information as well as information about Members, Committees, and Organizations of

 the House and to other U.S. government information resources. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.senate.gov/">The United States Senate</A> Information from and about the members of the Senate, Senate Committees, and Senate leadership and support offices. This evolving service also provides general background information about U.S.

 Senate legislative procedures, Senate facilities in the U.S. Capitol, and the history of the Senate.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.peacecorps.gov/">Peace Corps</A>
<P>
