<FONT SIZE=4>
/ <A HREF="art.html"> Art</A> / <A HREF="astronomy.html"> Astronomy  &AMP Space</A> / <A HREF="biology.html"> Biology</A> / <A HREF="chemistry.html"> Chemistry</A> / <A HREF="computers.html"> Computers</A> / <A HREF="dictionary.html"> Dictonaries &amp References</A> / <A HREF="environment.html"> Environment</A> / <A HREF="geography.html"> Geography</A> / <A HREF="geology.html"> Geology</A> / <A HREF="government.html"> Government</A> / <A HREF="history.html"> History</A>  / <A HREF="internet.html"> Internet Search</A> / <A HREF="libraries.html"> Libraries</A> / <A HREF="literature.html"> Literature</A>  / <A HREF="math.html"> Math</A> / <A HREF="museums.html"> Museums</A> / <A HREF="music.html"> Music</A>  / <A HREF="news.html"> News &amp Current events</A>  / <A HREF="perform.html"> Performing Arts</A> / <A HREF="physics.html"> Physics</A> / <A HREF="weather.html">  Weather</A> /
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="http://coombs.anu.edu.au/WWWVL-Aboriginal.html">Aboriginal Studies</A> This document keeps track of leading information
facilities in the field of Australian Aboriginal studies as well as the Indigenous/Native Peoples
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.sas.upenn.edu/African_Studies/AS.html">African Studies</A> African Studies Center World-Wide Web server at the University of Pennsylvania
<P>
<A HREF="http://www-oi.uchicago.edu/OI/DEPT/RA/ABZU/ABZU.HTML">ABZU</A>
Guide to resources for the study of the Ancient Near East available on the Internet 
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.tulane.edu/pompeii/text/mosaic.html">Alexander and Darius at the Battle of Issus</A> This mosaic depicts a battle between Alexander the Great and the Persian king Darius, probably the Battle of the Issus River in November of 333 B.C. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://rs6.loc.gov/amhome.html">American Memory</A> consists of collections of primary source and archival material relating to American culture and history.  
<P>
<A 
HREF="http://info-center.ccit.arizona.edu/~dante/sci_and_hum/cosmology.html"> 
History of Cosmology</A> <P>
<A href="http://sunsite.unc.edu/expo/1492.exhibit/Intro.html">1492: An Ongoing Voyage</a> A Library of Congress exhibit on the discovery of America
<P>
<A href="http://www.lib.uconn.edu/ArchNet/">ArchNet</A> ArchNet serves as the World Wide Web Virtual Library for Archaeology. This server provides access to
 archaeological resources available on the Internet.Catalan, Dutch, French, German, Italian, and Spanish language versions of the home page are also available. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.law.emory.edu/FEDERAL/usconst.html">Constitution of the United States</A>
<P> 
<A HREF="http://www.ucsc.edu/civil-war-letters/home.html">Letters from an Iowa Soldier in the Civil War</A>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.idbsu.edu/courses/hy309/">Electric Renaissance</A>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.law.emory.edu/FEDERAL/independ/declar.html">Declaration of Independence</A>
<P>
<A HREF="http://192.253.114.31/D-Day/Table_of_Contents.html">D-Day</A> World War II a collection of material created by the students and faculty of Patch High School and Patch Elementary School
<p>
<A href="http://dmf.culture.fr/culture/gvpda-en.htm">Discovery of a Palaeolithic painted cave</A> Descriptions and pictures of 20,000 year old cave art recently found in the South of France
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.teleport.com/~ddonahue/egyptol.html">Egyptology 
resources</A> 
Pharoah's Heart provides a World Wide Web resource for Egyptological 
information. <P>
<A href="http://grid.let.rug.nl/~welling/usa/revolution.html">From Revolution to Reconstruction</a> American history, from the colonial period until modern Times 
<P>
<A HREF="http://neal.ctstateu.edu:80/history/world_history/index.html">Gateway to World History</A> Provides resources to support the study and teaching of world history and history in general.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www1.huji.ac.il/jeru">Jerusalem Mosaic</A>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.georgetown.edu/labyrinth/labyrinth-home.html">Labyrinth</A> A World Wide Web Server for Medieval Studies Sponsored by Georgetown University
<P>
<A href="http://www.mecc.com/mayaquest.html">MayaQuest'96</a> In the spring of 1995, a team of five explorers, lead by Dan Buettner, bicycled to ruins in Mexico and Central America, met with on-site archaeologists, and attempted to unlock one of the most 





perplexing mysteries: the collapse of the ancient Maya civilization. But the team wasn't alone: over 1 million kids, teachers and others from around the globe helped to lead the expedition by way of the Internet. You can Join the Team.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.si.edu/nmai/">National Museum of the American Indian</A> The Smithsonian's National Museum of the American Indian is dedicated to the preservation, study, and exhibition of the life,   languages,literature, history, and arts of Native 





Americans.
<P>
<A HREF="http://web.maxwell.syr.edu/nativeweb">NativeWeb</A>

<P>
<A href="http://www.tiac.net/users/parallax/"> Notable Citizens of the Planet Earth</A> The Biographical Dictionary contains biographical information on over 18,000 people from ancient times to the present 
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/">Perseus Project Home Page</A> An Evolving Digital Library on Ancient Greece 
<P>
<A href="http://www.crs4.it/~luigi/SARDEGNA/sardegna.html">The History of Sardinia</A> 
<p>
<A HREF="http://pharos.bu.edu/Egypt/Wonders/">The Seven Wonders of the Ancient World</A> 
<P>
<a href="http://nmnhwww.si.edu">The Smithsonian Institution</a>  National Musem Of Natural History Web Home Page
<P>
<a href="http://sunsite.unc.edu/expo/deadsea.scrolls.exhibit/intro.html">Scrolls From The Dead Sea</A> An Exhibit at the Library of Congress, Washington, DC
<P>
<A HREF="http://mars.superlink.net/user/fsu/philo.html">Su Tzu's Chinese Philosophy Page</A> This page has been designed for the purpose of organizing the resources on Chinese philosophy that can be found in the 'cyberspace'.
 <P>
<A href="http://sunsite.unc.edu/expo/vatican.exhibit/exhibit/Main_Hall.html">The Vatican Exhibit Rome Reborn</a> 
<P>
<A href="http://www.demon.co.uk/history/">The World of the Vikings</A> The definitive guide to Vikings resources on the internet since 1994
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.times.st-pete.fl.us/treasures/TC.Lobby.html">Treasures of the Czars</A>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.gatech.edu/bgsa/blackpages.html">Universal Black Pages</A> Discover the African Diaspor
<P>
<A href="gopher://wiretap.Spies.COM:70/11/Gov/US-History">US Historical Documents</A> A collection of Historical documents from US history
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.voxpop.org/zipper/">Zipper</A> Find out who your Representatives and Senators are by entering your zip code Phone number fax and E-mail number of your Representative provided.
<P>
