<IMG SRC="math.gif"><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>

<FONT SIZE=4>

/ <A HREF="art.html"> Art</A> / <A HREF="astronomy.html"> Astronomy  &AMP Space</A> / <A HREF="biology.html"> Biology</A> / <A HREF="chemistry.html"> Chemistry</A> / <A HREF="computers.html"> Computers</A> / <A HREF="dictionary.html"> Dictonaries &amp References</A> / <A HREF="environment.html"> Environment</A> / <A HREF="geography.html"> Geography</A> / <A HREF="geology.html"> Geology</A> / <A HREF="government.html"> Government</A> / <A HREF="history.html"> History</A>  / <A HREF="internet.html"> Internet Search</A> / <A HREF="libraries.html"> Libraries</A> / <A HREF="literature.html"> Literature</A>  / <A HREF="math.html"> Math</A> / <A HREF="museums.html"> Museums</A> / <A HREF="music.html"> Music</A>  / <A HREF="news.html"> News &amp Current events</A
>  / <A HREF="perform.html"> Performing Arts</A> / <A HREF="physics.html"> Physics</A> / <A HREF="weather.html">  Weather</A> /
<BR><P>
<A HREF="ask.html"><IMG ALT="Ask Mr. Bohr" SRC="sbohrbnr.gif"></A>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P>
<A href="http://e-math.ams.org/">American Mathematical Society</A>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.tc.cornell.edu/Edu/MathSciGateway/index.html">Cornell Theory Center Math and Science Gateway</A> This Gateway provides links to resources in mathematics and science for educators and students in grades 9-12
<P>
<A HREF="http://sunsite.unc.edu/expo/vatican.exhibit/exhibit/d-mathematics/Greek_math2.html">Greek Mathematics and its Modern Heirs</A> Classical Roots of the Scientific Revolution
<P>
<A href="http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk:80/~history/">History of Mathematics Archive</a> The archive contains the biographies of more than 1100 mathematicians. We have recently reorganised it so that all the mathematicians now have individual biograph









ies and have added more extensive references. You can access them from a
selection of Alphabetical or Chronological Biographical indexes. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://mathserv.math.sfu.ca/Animations/animations.html">Mathematical Animation Gallery</A>
<P>
<A href="http://sunsite.unc.edu/expo/vatican.exhibit/exhibit/d-mathematics/Mathematics.html">Mathematics</A>  Including Greek Mathematics, Ptolemy's Geography, Greek Astronomy. 
<P>
<A href="http://daisy.uwaterloo.ca:80/~alopez-o/math-faq/">Frequently Asked Questions in Mathematics</A> This is a compilation of Frequently Asked Questions (and their answers) about Mathematics. Topics range from trivia and the trivial to advanced subjec









ts such as Wiles recent proof of Fermat's Last Theorem. 

<p>
<A href="http://math.furman.edu/~mwoodard/mquot.html">
Mathematical Quotation Server</A>  Furman University. A collection of mathematical quotations.
<p>
<a href="http://www.c3.lanl.gov/mega-math/welcome.html">
MegaMath</a> The MegaMath project is intended to bring unusual and
important mathematical ideas to elementary school classrooms so that young people and their teachers can think about them together.
<p>
<A href="http://www.utm.edu/research/primes/largest.html">
The Largest Known Primes</A> Information about prime numbers. 
<P>
<a href="http://www.ccsf.caltech.edu/ismap/image.html">
Xmorphia</a> Xmorphia is intended to show the variety of patterns that may be exhibited by a relatively simple parabolic partial differential equation
<P>
<BR>
<Font Size=5> Algebra &amp Geometry</Font>
<Font Size=4>
<p>
<P>
<A href="http://www.comlab.ox.ac.uk/oucl/users/jonathan.bowen/algebra/">A Brief History of Algebra and Computing</A> 
<P>
<A href="http://www.geom.umn.edu/">The Geometry Center</A>
The University of Minnesota includes interactive web applications such as math you can manipulate. Multimedia documents, a Geometry Reference Archives,graphic images, formulas, downloadable software, video productions and more
<P> 
<A href="http://www.forum.swarthmore.edu/">The Math Forum</A>
 Search or Browse The math Forum Internet Resource Collection
<P>
<A href="http://freeabel.geom.umn.edu/docs/forum/">The GeometryForum</a> The Geometry Forum is an electronic community focused on geometry and math education based at Swarthmore college.
The Forum began as a set of newsgroups, but now includes a WWW server and several other math-related services. 
<P>
<A href="http://life.anu.edu.au/complex_systems/tutorial3.html">Fractals and scale</A> An introduction to fractals
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu:80/Edu/Fractal/Fractal_Home.html">Fractal Microscope</A> 
<p>
<A href="http://spanky.triumf.ca/">The Spanky Fractal Database</A> This is a collection of fractals and fractal related material for free distribution on the net.
<BR>
<P>
<HR>
<Font Size=5> Math Is Fun</Font>
<Font Size=4>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.spiders.com/cgi-bin/countdown">Countdown</A>
How many seconds have you been alive? Find out how many seconds till your birthday or the year 2000.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.mathpro.com/math/mathCenter.html">Internet Center for Mathematics Problems</A> A list of mathematics problems and puzzles available on the Internet
<P>
<A HREF="http://juniper.tc.cornell.edu:8000/spiro/spiro.html">WWW spirograph.</A>
<P> 
<a href="http://www.scri.fsu.edu/~dennisl/topics/math_magic.html">
Cyberspace Middle School's Math Magic Activities</a> The nine magic tricks 
described 
here are all based on simple mathematics and not on magic </BLOCKQUOTE>
