</CENTER>
<P>
<br>
<P>
<a href="http://www.emerald.net/cf/cv.htm">The Culture Finder</a> A cultural event database which contains schedule information for over 500 orchestras, opera companies, ballet, dance companies and performing arts series, making it the most comprehensive 

and easily accessible source for cultural event information in
existence.
<P>
<p>
<A HREF="http://gopher.nypl.org/branch/central_units/my/parc.html">The New York Public 
Library for the Performing Arts</A>
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.lib.ohio-state.edu/OSU_profile/Music_Lib/">Ohio
State University Music &amp; Dance Library</A>
<p>
<BR>
<Font Size=5> Classical Music </FONT>
<Font Size=4>
<P>
<a href="http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/users/mn200/music/composers.html">
Classical Composers Biographies</a> Biographies and images 
<P>
<a href="http://www.einet.net/galaxy/Leisure-and-Recreation/Music/douglas-bell/Index.html"> Classical Music on the Internet</a> A quick and easy way to find classical music resources.
<P>
<a href="http://www.classical.net/music/">Classical Net Home page</a>The purpose of this home page is to provide a point-of-entry into a wide array of informational files
about classical music, includes Basic Repertoire List, Classical CD Buying Guide, Recommended Classical CDs, Composer Data, Reviews & Articles 
<P>
<a href="http://www.ipl.org/exhibit/mushist/">Music History 101</a>
Being a Survey of Western Classical Music with an Emphasis on the Landmark Works of the Great Composers, and on stylistic trends in Music from the Renaissance to the Present.
<P>
<a href="http://www.gprep.pvt.k12.md.us/classical/">The World-Wide Web Virtual Library:Classics</a> The classical music department of the WWW Virtual Library!
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<Font Size=5> Dance </FONT>
<Font Size=4>
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.thepoint.net/~raw/dance.htm">CyberDance - Ballet on the Net</A> This is a collection of links to classical ballet and modern dance resources on the Internet. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.cyberspace.com/vandehey/dance.html">Dance Directory at www.cyberspace.com</A> Index includes Ballet and Modern Dance, Ballroom Dance, Contra Dance, Directories Folk Dance ,Historical Dance, Morris Dancing, Square Dance, Swing and Lindy

, Tango and more 
<P>
<A HREF="http://ireland.iol.ie/~dance/">Dance In Ireland</A>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.tmn.com/Artswire/www/dance/browse.html">Dancin On The Web</A> 
<p>
<a href="http://bohr.physics.purdue.edu:80/~jswhite/dance_links.html">Dance Links</a>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.ivo.se/as-sayf/bellies.html">Oriental Dance on the Web</A>
<P>
<A HREF="http://emporium.turnpike.net/~dpd/index.htm">Worldwide DancePages Directory</A> The directory contains information on contemporary choreographers and dance companies worldwide and is structured geographically. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Entertainment/Dance/">Yahoo's Index of Dance URLs</A>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<Font Size=5> Opera </FONT>
<Font Size=4>
<p>
<A HREF= 
"http://www.music.sony.com/Music/ArtistInfo/KaritaMattila_Biography.html">Karita Mattila</A>
<A href=http://joshua.micronet.it/italian/mariobiondi/opere/diz_opera_.html> Recorded &amp Broadcasted Opera Dictionary</A> by Mario Biondi
<P>
<a href="http://rick.stanford.edu/opera/main.html">OperaGlass</a> An opera information server on the World Wide Web. Here you can get detailed information, including performance histories, synopses, libretti, discographies, pictures, and more on any of as

mall but rapidly growing number of operas, plus pointers to many other opera servers. 
<P>
<A HREF= http://copper.ucs.indiana.edu/~lneff/libretti.html>Opera
Libretti</A> Public-Domain Opera Libretti and Other
Vocal Texts
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.doit.it/OperaWeb/English/OperaWeb.html">OperaWeb</A> Available in English and Italian - a Great source of information on Opera. Includes an Interactive quiz and  sing a-long.
<P>
<A HREF="http://orathost.cfa.ilstu.edu/public/oratGallery/FacultyStudentWebPages/rrepp/vocal/muslink.html">Muslink</A>

<A HREF="http://www.geko.net.au/~anr/3tenors.htm">THE 3 TENORS</A>
Information on the International Tour of the famous operatic trio; JOSE CARRERAS, PLACIDO DOMINGO and LUCIANO PAVAROTTI. Includes photo images and biographies of The 3 Tenors.

<P>
<A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Arts/Drama/Opera/">Yahoo Opera Page</A>
<P>
<HR>
<p>
<Font Size=5> Theatre </FONT>
<Font Size=4>
<p>

<A HREF="http://www.ex.ac.uk/drama/tech/glossary.html">Glossary of Technical Theatre Terms</A> Compiled by Jon Primrose
<P>
<A HREF="http://the-tech.mit.edu/Shakespeare/works.html">
The Complete Works of William Shakespeare</A> 
<p>
<A HREF="http://english-server.hss.cmu.edu/Drama.html">The English Server:Drama</A> This directory contains a number of plays, screenplays and discussions of drama and dramatic productions.
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.theatre-central.com/">Theatre Central</A> A large directory of theatre related information and theatre groups
</BLOCKQUOTE>
