<HTML>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" Background="einyspiralbk.gif" TEXT="#3300FF" 
LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#009C00" ALINK="#FFCCOO">
<HEAD><TITLE>Einsteins Chalkboard..Geography..SERVDirect</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<META http-equiv="PICS-Label" content='(PICS-1.0 
"http://www.rsac.org/ratingsv01.html" 1 gen true comment "RSACi North 
America Server" by "mark@sdirect.com" for "http://sdirect.com/einstein" 
on "1996.04.04T08:15-0500" exp "1997.01.01T08:15-0500" r (n 0 s 0 v 0 1 
0))'>
<META http-equiv="PICS-Label" 
content='(PICS-1.0 "http://www.classify.org/safesurf/" l gen t for
"http://http://www.sdirect.com/einstein/" r (SS~~000 1 SS~~100 1))'>
<meta name="rating" content="safe for kids">
<body>
<CENTER>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="geography.gif"><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=4>
/ <A HREF="art.html"> Art</A> / <A HREF="astronomy.html"> Astronomy  &AMP Space</A> / <A HREF="biology.html"> Biology</A> / <A HREF="chemistry.html"> Chemistry</A> / <A HREF="computers.html"> Computers</A> / <A HREF="dictionary.html"> Dictonaries &amp References</A> / <A HREF="environment.html"> Environment</A> / <A HREF="geography.html"> Geography</A> / <A HREF="geology.html"> Geology</A> / <A HREF="government.html"> Government</A> / <A HREF="history.html"> History</A>  / <A HREF="internet.html"> Internet Search</A> / <A HREF="libraries.html"> Libraries</A> / <A HREF="literature.html"> Literature</A>  / <A HREF="math.html"> Math</A> / <A HREF="museums.html"> Museums</A> / <A HREF="music.html"> Music</A>  / <A HREF="news.html"> News &amp Current events</A
>  / <A HREF="perform.html"> Performing Arts</A> / <A HREF="physics.html"> Physics</A> / <A HREF="weather.html">  Weather</A> /
</CENTER>
</FONT>
<BR>
<p>
<p>
<FONT SIZE=4>
<A HREF=http://www.city.net/>City.Net</A> A  guide to communities around the world. City.Net is updated every day to provide easy and timely access to information on travel, entertainment, and local business, plus government and community services. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://info.er.usgs.gov/fact-sheets/finding-your-way/finding-your-way.html"> Finding Your Way with Map and Compass</A> Teaches you how to use a map and compass.
<P>
<A HREF=http://wings.buffalo.edu/geogw>Geographic Name Server Xerox Map Gateway</A> This searchable index contains almost all U.S. cities and towns, and a few cities outside the U.S.  This is a gateway between the Geographic Name Server at martini.eecs.um

ich.edu and the World Wide Web, with links to maps from Xerox.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.indo.com/distance/">How far is it?</A> This service uses the University of Michigan Geographic Name Server and a supplementary database of world cities to find the latitude and longitude of two places, and then calculates the distance 

between them (as the crow flies). It also provides a map showing the two places, using the Xerox PARC Map Server. 
<P>
<A
HREF="http://nearnet.gnn.com/gnn/meta/travel/res/countries.html"> A world travel guide.</A>
<p>
<a href="http://www.adfa.oz.au/CS/flg/index.html">World Flags</A>
<P>
<A HREF=http://pubweb.parc.xerox.com/map/>World Map (Xerox PARC Map Viewer)</A>
<P>
<p>
<a href="http://loki.ur.utk.edu/ut2kids/maps/map.html">Mapmaker, Mapmaker, Make Me a Map</a> A great introduction to maps and cartography
<p>
<a href="http://pubweb.parc.xerox.com/map/">Map Viewer</a> The Xerox PARC Map Viewer is a World-Wide Web HTTP server that accepts requests for a World or USA map and returns an HTML documen including an image of the requested map. Each map image is create

d on demand from a geographic database. 
<p>
<A href="http://wings.buffalo.edu/world/vt2/">
The Virtual Tourist</a> A map-based interface to general information, tourist guides, and pictures for places all over the world
<p>
<a href="http://info.er.usgs.gov/fact-sheets/maps-us/index.html">
Maps of the United States</A> US Geological Survey 
<p>
<P>
<a href="http://wings.buffalo.edu/geogw">US Gazetter</a> Search for the locations of towns in the United States
<P>
<A HREF="http://info.er.usgs.gov/">The U.S. Geological Survey home page</A> U. S. Geological Survey, a bureau of the Department of the Interior. USGS is the Nation's largest earth science research and information agency.Information on geology, mapping, an

d water resources.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>

</Font>
