<P>
<Font Size=5> Poetry </Font>
<Font Size=4>
<p>
<a href="http://www.primenet.com/~sburr/verses.html">A Child's Garden of
Verses</a>
<P>
<a href="http://english-server.hss.cmu.edu/Poetry.html">The English Server - Poetry</A> A collection of poetry 
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.vive.com/connect/walt/whit.htm">Walt Whitman Circle Home Page</A> This home page is dedicated to all who would like to expand their poetic horizons, and learn more
about America's most famous poet, and the times he lived in.
<P>
<A HREF="http://icg.harvard.edu/~cather/">Willa Cather Page</A> Material by and about this 1923 Pulitzer-prize winning novelist &AMP poet. 
<P>
<A href="http://mikan.cc.matsuyama-u.ac.jp:80/~shiki/">The Shiki Internet Haiku Salon</A> Shiki Masaoka, the haiku poet, was born in Matsuyama in 1867. Shiki is well known in Japan for
introducing a new style of haiku, a short poetic form,
and for enhancing the arts.
<p>
<A href="http://sunsite.unc.edu/dykki/poetry/home.html">
The Internet Poetry Archive</A> The University of North Carolina Press joins the UNC Office of Information Technology in publishing the Internet Poetry Archive. The archive will make available over a worldwide > <HR><H3>Transfer interrupted!</H3> 
