<P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE =5>
<B>
/ <A HREF="gameslinks.html">Games</A>  / <A HREF="riddles.html">Riddles &AMP Jokes</A>  / <A HREF="project.html"> Project Center</A>  / <A HREF="sports.html"> Sports</A>  /</Center>

<p>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=5>W</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=4><B>elcome to the games page here in Einstein's Chalkboard. If you know of a fun interactive web game site <a href="email.html">email us</a> and let us know so we can add it to our list.
<BR>
<P>
<a href="http://204.194.39.10">Anarchy Garden</a> runs Tsarwars, a free,
multiplayer, strategy game.  Tsarwars is played over the Internet using
a web browser or a telnet client.  New users can play on their first
connection.
<P>
<a href="http://cvs.anu.edu.au/andy/rid/riddle.html">3D riDDle</a> Navigate through a number of pages by solving three-dimensional riddles. On each page you have to solve a little puzzle hidden in a stereogram and - based on the outcome - choose one of fo





ur links to other pages, only one of which leads closer to the goal.
<P>                                     
<a href="http://www.rahul.net/renoir/monster/monster.html">Build-a-Monster</a> By DroidWorks. Great for young kids
<p>
<a href="http://www.dtd.com/ace/">Bullpen Ace</a> The baseball trivia challenge where you test your baseball knowledge!
<P>
<a href="http://caissa.com">Caissa's Web</a> An internet chess server on the Web. Serving up over 250 live games per day!
<P>
<a href="http://studwww.rug.ac.be/cgi-bin/cgiwrap?user=mjdbruyn&script=chessweb.cgi">ChessWeb</a> By Marc de Bruyne. An open chess game; anyone can make a move.
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.cs.uidaho.edu/~casey931/conway/games.html">Clever Games for Clever People</A> These games are all taken from:
Conway, John. 1976. On Numbers and Games. New York: Academic Press, Inc. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://csugrad.cs.vt.edu/htbin/Connect4.perl">Connect Four</A> By Joe Hines and Brian Roder. Connect Four pieces in a row and you win. You can connect four in a row horizontaly, vertically, or diagonally. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.cyberjacques.com">Cyber Jacques' Cyber Seas Treasure Hunt</A> Includes Simon Says, Connect the Dots, Hangman, Plank, JumperSecret, WordTangram, GameTile Puzzle and more!
<P>
 <a href="http://www.dtd.com/bug/">Dr. Fellowbug's Laboratory of Fun and
Horror</a>
<P>
<A HREF="http://postcards.www.media.mit.edu/Postcards/">Electric Postcard</A> You pick the card you like, write your message, and send it off. The recipient will be notified by email that a card has
been sent and to claim it at the Pick-up Window.
<P>
<a href="http://www.hmco.com/hmco/school/dictionary/index.html">Fake Out!</a> The  dictionary guessing game. Games are matched to grade levels k-2 thru 6th and up.
<p>

<A HREF="http://www.gamesdomain.com/">Games Domain</A> The site is designed to be a central reference point for all things "games-related" on the Internet. 
<P>
<a href="http://main.street.net/arcade/JEM-maze/">HTML Maze</a> By James McNalley 
<P>
<a href="http://www.bu.edu/htbin/wcl/">Hunt the Wumpas</a>
<P>
<a href="http://rr-vs.informatik.uni-ulm.de/rrbin/ui/RRPage.html">Interactive Model Railroad</a> At Universit&auml;t Ulm in Germany.  Run the train and watch the video results
<P>
<p>
<a href="http://www.wordsmith.org/awad-cgibin/anagram">Internet Anagram Server</a> By Anu Garg. Transpose the letters of a word or phrase and find out what new words you get. Fun!
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.hydra.com/icc/">Internet Chess Club</A> The world's most active chess club! Over 5,000 chess games played daily! 
 <P>
<a href="http://www.littlejason.com/lemonade/index.html">Lemonade</a> By 
Jason Mayans <p>
<P>
<a href="http://www.ntua.gr/mandel/mandel.html">Mandelbrot Explorer</a> by Panagiotis Christias</a>
<P>
<a href="http://www.bu.edu/htbin/mines">Minesweeper</a>
<P>
<a href="http://winnie.acsu.buffalo.edu/potatoe/">Mr. Edible Starchy Tuber Head</a>
<P>
<A href="http://imagiware.com/nowhere.cgi"> Nowwwhere</A>  A web-accessible virtual world that features 3-D ray-traced graphics,
multi-user interaction, animation, sound, and other neat stuff. 

<a href="http://www.webplayer.com/'>Onslaught</A> A graphical multiplayer web game,which allows you to play against other human opponents, from all over the world, in real time.
<P>
<a href="http://rhf.bradley.edu/~primal1/pegs.html">Pegs</a> By Scott Reynen. Several peg puzzles
<P>
<a href="http://www.pres96.com/index.html">President '96</a>
<P>
<a href="http://www.triangle-st.com/gallery.html">Puzzle Gallery</a>  By Triangle Street Diversions</a> Clocked Out, Bookworm,
Lead-Free Wordplay, puzzles and much more! 
<p>
<a href="http://www.tne.com/~janus/puzzle/ppage.htm">Puzzle Page</a>
<P>
<a href=http://www.vikora.com/Namaste/Rambhoja/>Rambhoja and The Search for the Treasures of India</a>  An educational, interactive game about India.  Lots of fun!
<P>
<a href=http://www.cs.utoronto.ca/~riedel/rubik/rubik.html>Rubik's
Cube</a>
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.sartelle.org/Sim/">SimCity 2000 Gallery </A>
<P>
<a
href="http://www.stardot.com/~lukeseem/stubbed.html">Stubbed Toe</a>  Tic Tac Toe
<P>
<a href="http://www.dtd.com/tmw/">Two Minute Warning</a > The NFL trivia game.
<p>
<a href="http://www2.smart.net/mcurtis-cgi-bin/slider.html">Slider Puzzle</a> The 16-puzzle By Mike Curtis
<P>
<a href="http://genesis.tiac.net/puzzle.html">The 16 puzzle</a> By Steve Belcz. This is an HTML version of those little toy puzzles with the sliding plastic squares. The object is to move the squares around to put all the letters in order or  to complete 

an image. 
<p>
<a href="http://www.familygames.com">Family Games</a> By Aha Software 
<P>
<a href="http://ugweb.cs.ualberta.ca/~hubick/digzone/digzone.cgi"> The Dig
Zone</a> Created by Chris HubickDig Zone is a multi-user shared 
environment where it is your mission to safely pilot your player through  
the many hazards of gravity in search of valuable coins.

<P>
<a href="http://www.hmco.com/school/geo/indexhi.html">The GeoNet Game</a>  A geography triva game for children in grades 4 and above. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.girlgamesinc.com/puzzler.html">The Puzzler</A> By Girl Games,Inc. Brain Teasers
<P>
<a href="http://http.bsd.uchicago.edu/~e-pikat/TicTacToe/ttt.html">Tic Tac Toe</a> The  classic game of X's and O's.
<p>
<a href="http://ix.urz.uni-heidelberg.de:8080/Christian/TicTacToe.html">Tic Tac Toe</a> By Christan Jung
<p>
<a href="http://ZOO.CS.YALE.EDU:8000/~miller/trivia/">Trivia Ink</a>
 By Adam Millers an interactive page where you, the user, get to answer trivia collected from people all over the web.
<P>
<a href="http://www.tvland.com">TV Land</a>
contains a few games, including Escape the TV Land Stalag, Find the Genie in the Bottle, TV Land of the Giants 
<P>
<a href="http://www.hmco.com/school/tales/">Wacky Web Tales</a> By Houghton Mifflin
<p>
<a href="http://info.gte.com/gtel/fun/battle/battle.html">WebBattleship</a> By Steve Belczyk
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.statslab.cam.ac.uk/~sret1/backgammon/main.html">WWWBackgammon Page</A>
<P>
<a href="http://info.gte.com/gtel/fun/mines/mines.html">WebMineSweeper</a>
<P>
<a href="http://info.gte.com/gtel/fun/maze/maze.html">WYSH</a> By
Steve Belczyk. An Interactive maze
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.statslab.cam.ac.uk/~sret1/backgammon/main.html">WWWBackgammon Page</A> Includes pointers to all of the most popular backgammon resources on the Internet, as well as lots of information on backgammom
<P>
<a href="http://juniper.tc.cornell.edu:8000/spiro/spiro.html">WWW Spirograph</a> By Jeffrey Cohen
<P>
<a href="http://www.yahoo.com/Recreation/Games/Internet_Games/Interactive_Web_Games/">Interactive Web Games list by Yahoo.com</a> 
