<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<center><font size=5> The Answers </font></center>
<font size=4>
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="butterflys">1.</a> What do butterflys sleep on?<BR>
A caterpiller.
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="need">2.</a> What do you throw out when you need it and take in when you don't need it? <BR>
 An anchor
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="parrot">3.</a> What do you get when you cross a tiger with a parrot?<BR>
I don't know but when he talks you had better listen!
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="dracula">4.</a> Why is Dracula so unpopular? 
<BR>
 Because he is such a pain in the neck
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="trunk">5.</a> Why do elephants have trunks? 
<BR>
 Because they'd look really silly carrying  a suitcase!
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="skunks">6.</a> Why are skunks so smart? 
<BR>
 Because they have a lot of scents.
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="20,000">7.</a> What is convenient and weighs 20,000 pounds?
<BR>
 An elephant six-pack.
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="bronto">8.</a> What is as big as a brontosauraus but weighs nothing? 
<BR>
 His shadow
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="diamond">9.</a> What is the biggest diamond in the world? 
<BR>
 The baseball diamond.
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<a name="smoke">10.</a> If an electric train is going west, which direction is the  smoke  going? 
<BR>
 Electric trains do not have have smoke.
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<a name="Route66">11.</a> What was the elephant doing on Route 66?<BR>
 About 4 miles an hour.
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="indian">12.</a> What is the difference between an Indian elephant and an African elephant? 
<BR>
 About three thousand miles.
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="birds">13.</a> Why do birds fly south for the winter? 
<BR>
 It's too far to walk!
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="bow">14.</a> What type of bow is impossible to tie? 
<BR>
A rainbow 
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="math">15.</a> Why is math a heavy subject? 
<BR>
 Because of all the numbers you have to carry!!!
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="sailors">16.</a> Why couldn't the sailors play cards? <BR> Because the Captain was standing on the deck.
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="baby">17.</a> Why is a baby like an old car?<BR> 
They both have a rattle!
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="overhead">18.</a> What goes over your head and under your feet? <BR>
A skipping rope.
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="runs">19.</a> It runs all day and never walks. Often murmurs, never talks. It has a bed and never sleeps. It has a mouth and never eats. What is it? <BR>
 A river
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="fishing">20.</a> There were two fathers and two sons fishing  together at a lake one day. Each of them caught a fish but when they arrived home, they only had three fish. How could this be?
<BR>
   One was the grandfather,one was the father and one was the son. (two of them were sons and two of them were fathers)
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="world">21.</a> What goes all around the world but still stays stuck in one place? <BR>
  A stamp
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="squirrel">22.</a> How do you catch a squirrel? 
<BR>
  Act like a nut and he'll follow you anywhere!
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="cross">23.</a> Why did the elephant cross the road? 
<BR>
 It was the chicken's day off.
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="rain">24.</a> What goes up when the rain comes down?<BR>
An umbrella
<BR>
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="talk">25.</a> How do elephants talk to each other?<BR>
By 'elephone of course!
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="legs">26.</a> What walks on four legs in the morning, two legs in the afternoon, and three legs in the evening? 
<BR>
A person, because a person crawls on all fours as a baby, walks on two legs as an adult, and uses a cane in old age. 
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="eye">27.</a> What has an eye but can not cry? <BR>
A needle.
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="roof">28.</a> If a rooster lays an egg on the top of the barn, would the egg fall down the north or south side of the roof? <BR>
Neither direction because roosters don't lay eggs
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="fridge">29.</a> How can you tell if there is an elephant in your refrigerator?<BR>
You can see his footprints in the butter.
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="hat">30.</a>  What time is it when an elephant sits on your hat? <BR>
It's time to get a new hat!
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="fish">31.</a> What do you call a fish with no eye? <BR>
A  fsh!
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="dad">32.</a> Why did the dad wear a bathing suit to work?<BR>
Because he was in a car pool!
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="lighter">33.</a> What weighs nothing, can be seen by the naked eye, and  can make anything lighter? <BR>
A hole! 
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="chat">34.</a> What did one eye say to the other?<BR>
Between you and me something smells!
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="head">35.</a> What has a head and a tail but no body? <BR>
A coin! 
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="tallest">36.</a> What is the tallest building in the world?<BR>
A library because it has so many stories 
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="apple">37.</a> What is worse than finding a worm in an apple? <BR>
Finding  just half of a worm in an apple.
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="dinner">38.</a> What did the skeleton use to impress his dinner guest? <BR>
His bone china
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="cook">39.</a> What did the eggs say to the cook?<BR> 
You crack me up!
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="serve">40.</a> What do you serve but never eat? <BR>
A tennis ball!
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="day">41</a> What day of the week do fish hate most? <BR>
Fry - day!
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="cake">42.</a> What do you call a crazy cake? <BR>
A dough-nut.
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="dog">43.</a> What kind of dog wears a watch? <BR>
A watch dog.
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="wise">44.</a> What do you call a wise chicken?<BR>
An eggs-pert
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="snake">45.</a> Why is a snake so smart? <BR>
Because you can't pull his leg.
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="money">46.</a>  What type of money do birds use?<BR>
Bills
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="sack">47.</a> Who  always gets the sack as soon as he starts work ? <BR>
The Postman
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="sandwich">48.</a> What did one sandwich say to the other sandwich? <BR>
Could you sub for me?
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="belt">49.</a> What kind of belt does a planet wear? <BR>
 An astroid belt.
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="sea">50.</a> How do we know the sea is friendly? <BR>
Because it waves all the time !
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="speeds">51.</a> What driver never speeds? <BR>
A  screwdriver! 
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="occurs">52.</a> What occurs once in a minute, twice in a moment,but never in a thousand years? <BR>
The letter "M" 
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="tennies">53.</a>  Why do elephants wear tennies? <BR>
Because ninies are too small and elevensies are too big!
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="skelton">54.</a> Why didn't the skeleton cross the road? <BR>
Because he just didn't have the guts to do it. 
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="strawberry">55.</a> What did one strawberry say to the other strawberry? <BR>
If you were not so fresh we wouldn't be in this jam!
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="cow">56.</a> What do you get if you cross a duck and a cow?  <BR>
Quackers and milk.
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="coach">57.</a> What did the coach say to the telephone booth? <BR>
I want my quaterback!
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="gray">58.</a> What is gray, has big ears, a trunk, and weighs two ounces? <BR>
A mouse on vacation.
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="golfer">59.</a> Why did the golfer wear two pair of pants?<BR>
In case he got a hole in one!
<P><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="cucumber">60.</a> What did one cucumber say to the other cucumber? <BR>
If you were not so fresh we would'nt be in this pickle!
<P><FONT COLOR=YELLOW>
<BR>
<a name="girlscouts">61.</a> What do you call 12 girlscouts in a bakery? 
<BR>
A dozen brownies!
<P><FONT COLOR=MAGENTA>
<BR>
<a name="picture">62.</a>What did the picture say to the wall? 
<BR>
I have been framed!
<P><FONT COLOR=WHITE>
<BR>
<a name="up">63.</a>What goes up but never comes down?
<BR>
Your age!
<p><FONT COLOR=ORANGE>
<BR>
<a name="eyes">64.</a> What has four eyes but can not see?
<BR>
Mississippi 
<P>
<BR>
<P>
