<TITLE>
FOCUS: Toxic Tort
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="./images/cbs.gif" text="#000000" link="#f00000" vlink="#2f4f4f">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="./images/rglogo.gif" width="606" height="105">
</CENTER>
<B><IMG SRC="./images/toxic.gif" align="left" hspace="10" vspace="0" border="1" width="198" height="307"><font size="4">H</font>azardous chemicals and materials have no respect for boundary, age, or gender. In most cases, their effects are not seen or felt until long after the initial exposure has occured.

<P><font size="4">U</font>nder these circumstances, it is necessary to determine the facts, identify the responsible parties, and agressively pursue them in courts of law, using all available legal strategies and techniques to obtain justice and compensation for those who have been victimized.

<P><font size="4">R</font>obles &amp; <font size="4">G</font>onzalez has devoted a major portion of its practice to developing a system of capabilities and procedures that are suited specifically for this very purpose. The firm has represented thousands of victims in toxic tort cases involving substances such as asbestos, pesticides, and other hazardous chemicals.
</B>

