<TITLE>
About Robles &amp; Gonzalez
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="./images/cbs.gif" text="#000000" link="#f00000" vlink="#2f4f4f">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="./images/rglogo.gif" width="606" height="105">
</CENTER>
<B><IMG SRC="./images/r-g.gif" align="left" hspace="10" border="1" width="251" height="500"><font size="4">R</font>obles &amp; <font size="4">G</font>onzalez was founded in 1972. Today, the firm serves an international practice, with clients throughout the Western Hemisphere.

<P><font size="4">T</font>he firm's primary areas of practice are litigation and general civil law, with an emphasis on toxic tort, defective products and medical devices, railroad accidents, and other personal injuries. In addition, <font size="4">R</font>obles &amp; <font size="4">G</font>onzalez has experience in such areas as job-related accidents, employer discrimination, medical malpractice, and aviation disasters, as well as civil matters such as probate and business law.

<P><font size="4">T</font>he firm's client roster does not include large or multi-national corporations, or financial institutions, or "emerging" growth companies. Rather, litigation is undertaken on behalf of those who have been victimized by the actions of large companies and organizations: Workers who have been exposed to asbestos. Individuals who have been implanted with defective heart valves. Farmworkers whose lives have been unalterably changed through exposure to dangerous chemicals and pesticides. And those who have been injured in railroad, aviation, automobile, workplace, and other accidents.

<P><font size="4">M</font>embers of the firm are admitted to practice in Florida, Colorado, Texas, New York, and the District of Columbia. The firm also practices in other states through local counsel.

<P><font size="4">P</font>artners and associates at <font size="4">R</font>obles &amp; <font size="4">G</font>onzalez are supported by a highly-trained staff of paralegals, legal secretaries, and computer operators who utilize a comprehensive computer network comprised of state-of-the-art equipment and specialized software programs. In addition, the firm maintains an extensive law library, and computerized research terminals allow access to legal documents and other reference materials which provide additional assistance in solving complex legal problems. Related functions such as litigation support, case and calendar management, word and data processing, telegrams, telexes, timekeeping, and bookkeeping are all computerized and stored in-house, allowing the firm to efficiently manage cases and provide up-to-the-minute status reports and detailed billings for clients.</B>
