<TITLE>
$3 Million Damages in Asbestos Case
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#f00000" vlink="#2f4f4f">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="./images/asbestos.gif" width="387" height="67">

<table align=center units="pixels" width="400" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" border="0">
<tr>

<td valign=top width="400">
<P>TAMPA - A retired Sanford construction worker and his wife have been awarded $3 million by a jury in Hillsborough County Circuit Court for damages resulting from exposure to asbestos.

<P>Arthur Dougherty, 65, was awarded $2 million and his wife, Joan, was awarded $1 million following a week long trial.

<P>The defendants in the case were W.R. Grace &amp; Co., headquartered in Boca Raton, and Owens-Corning Fiberglass Corp., of Toledo, Ohio. The verdict, handed down Friday, cited both companies for negligence.


<P>Dougherty suffers from mesothelioma, a form of cancer which strikes the lining of the lungs. The couple's attorney, Ervin Gonzalez, claimed Dougherty's cancer is a result of the man's exposure to asbestos contained in materials manufactured by the defendant companies.

<P>"Long after it was known that asbestos had such dreadful side effects, many companies continued with its use simply because it was economical," said Gonzalez.

<P>The lawsuit was filed earlier this year.
</table>

<P>
<I>Tampa Tribune</I>, October 6, 1992<BR>


<A HREF="inthenew.html"><P><IMG SRC="./images/toindex.gif" border="0" width="173" height="20" hspace="10"></A>
<A HREF="contact1.html"><IMG SRC="./images/contact.gif" border="0" width="173" height="20" hspace="10"></A>
<A HREF="premail2.html"><IMG SRC="./images/sendmail.gif" border="0" width="173" height="20" hspace="10"></A>

