<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Arvida Settlement Amount Raised
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#f00000" vlink="#2f4f4f">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="./images/ftlnew.gif" width="338" height="86">

<table align=center units="pixels" width="400" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" border="0">
<tr>


<td valign=top width="400">
<P>By TRACY KOLODY<BR>Business Writer
<P>One of South Florida's largest home builders may end up paying more for damages stemming from Hurricane Andrew.

<P>According to a Miami Lawyer, the dollar amount of a hurricane-related settlement between the builder and uninsured condominium owners was raised on Wednesday.

<P>Ervin Gonzalez, who represents some of the homeowners at Country Walk, a hard-hit south Dade sub-division containing 1,300 homes, said the original settlement was modified to allow for higher payments to uninsured condominium owners.

<P>That proposed settlement is not related to a lawsuit filed against the builder by the condominium association at Village Homes of Country Walk, which deals strictly with common areas at affected buildings. That case was settled this week for $2.74 million.

<P>The original settlement, which was submitted to the 11th Circuit Court in Dade County on April 13 and is awaiting court approval, called for 87 single-family homeowners in Country Walk Estate and Pation Homes to each receive $7,500. And 135 condominium owners at Village Homes of Country Walk were to receive $4,500 each.

<P>But that amount was not enough for condo owners who were not insured for the loss of their belongings and personal property when Hurricane Andrew hit on Aug. 24, Gonzalez said.

<P>Company officials were not available for comment on Wednesday.

<P>Under terms of the revsion, Gonzalez said uninsured condominium owners will receive an additional $20,000.

<P>The attorney said he negotiated the revised settlement because he learned that 40 percent to 50 percent of the owners did not carry personal property insurance.



</table>

<P><I>The Sun Sentinel</I>, April 29, 1993<BR>


<A HREF="inthenew.html"><P><IMG SRC="./images/toindex.gif" border="0" width="173" height="20" hspace="10"></A>
<A HREF="contact1.html"><IMG SRC="./images/contact.gif" border="0" width="173" height="20" hspace="10"></A>
<A HREF="premail2.html"><IMG SRC="./images/sendmail.gif" border="0" width="173" height="20" hspace="10"></A>

</CENTER>
