</CENTER>
<IMG SRC="./images/robles.gif" align="left" hspace="10" vspace="0" border="1" width="136" height="193"><B><font size="4">L</font>ouis S. Robles received an undergraduate degree in business administration, with a major in economics, from the University of Florida in 1969, and a Juris Doctorate from the University of Florida Law School in 1971. Admitted to practice in Florida, Colorado, and Texas, Mr. Robles is a member of the Federal Trial Bars for the Southern and Middle Districts of Florida, and is admitted to practice before the United States Eleventh Circuit Court of Appeals. He is rated "AV" in the Martindale-Hubbell Law Directory, the highest rating available.

<P><font size="4">M</font>r. Robles is a member of the American Bar Association, the Association of Trial Lawyers of America, the Academy of Florida Trial Lawyers, the Florida Bar, the Environmental Law Section of the Florida Bar, the Dade County Bar Association, and the Greater Miami Chamber of Commerce. He also serves as special counsel to the Children's Resource Fund, and has been appointed to the National Asbestos Class Action Steering Committee.


