<HEAD>
<TITLE>
About Ervin A. Gonzalez
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="./images/cbs.gif" text="#000000" link="#f00000" vlink="#2f4f4f">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="./images/rglogo.gif" width="606" height="105">
</CENTER>
<IMG SRC="./images/gonzalez.gif" align="left" hspace="10" vspace="0" border="1" width="136" height="193"><B><font size="4">E</font>rvin A. Gonzalez earned a Juris Doctorate, cum laude, from the University of Miami School of Law. He has been a member of the Florida Bar since 1985, and is also admitted to practice in Washington, D.C., Texas, Colorado, New York, and before the U.S. Supreme Court. He is also a member of the Trial Bars for the Southern and Middle Districts of Florida, and the Southern District of Texas.

<P><font size="4">M</font>r. Gonzalez has been board certified as a specialist in civil trial law by the Florida Bar and the National Board of Trial Advocacy.  He is rated "AV" in the Martindale-Hubbell Law Directory, the highest rating available, and serves as the immediate past president of the Dade County Trial Lawyers Association and Treasurer of the Dade County Bar Association.  He also serves on the board of directors of the Academy of Florida Trial Lawyers, the Rules of Civil Procedure Committee of the Florida Bar Association, and as a member of the American Bar Association, the Association of Trial Lawyers of America and the Florida Bar Trial Lawyers' Section.  Mr. Gonzalez is also an adjunct professor at the University of Miami Law School, where he teaches a course on litigation skills.

<P><font size="4">M</font>r. Gonzalez has served as lead counsel on numerous class-action and consolidated cases, and has lectured and written about a wide range of legal issues.

