Navy News, the newspaper of the royal Navy since 1954, has half a million readers worldwide. Since it first entered the British association of Industrial Editors' Editing for Industry competition in 1972 it has won 71 awards without missing  a single year - a unique record.</P>

In 1996 it received an award for its first entry in the Plain English Campaign competition.</P>

