<H2>Latest News</H2>
<HR>
<A HREF="../archive/archive.htm" TARGET="contents"> News Archive</A>&#160;&#128;&#160;<A HREF="../navynews.htm" TARGET="contents"> Navy News</A>
<HR>
</P>

091/96

<H4>COMMERCIAL PARTNER FOR NAVAL TRAINING</H4>



A commercial partnering scheme between the Royal Navy and the Flagship Training consortium has been given the go-ahead, Minister of State for the Armed Forces Nicholas Soames announced recently.</P>

This decision allows the Naval Recruiting and Training Agency (NRTA) to enter a formal agreement with Flagship Training and develop implementation plans for each of the NRTA's shore training establishments, which should take around six months.</P>

A key element is the prospect of training "under the White Ensign" - drawing on the RN brand name and reputation for quality training. This could include expanding foreign training, apprentice-style technical training and personal development training.</P>

Mr Soames said: "This new arrangement provides a unique opportunity for the UK public and private defence sectors to work together in the world defence market and provide the right environment for substantial investment under the Government's Private Finance Initiative."</P>

<A HREF="../latest.htm" TARGET="contents"> Back to Latest News</A>

