<H2>Latest News</H2>
<HR>
<A HREF="../archive/archive.htm" TARGET="contents"> News Archive</A>&#160;&#128;&#160;<A HREF="../navynews.htm" TARGET="contents"> Navy News</A>
<HR></P>

130/96 


<H4>SEA HARRIER FA2 FIRST IN SERVICE FIRING OF AMRAAM</H4>



The Royal Navy carried out the first in service firing of the new Advanced Medium Range Air to Air Missile (AMRAAM) from the latest version of the Sea Harrier, the FA2.  </P>

The firing at the US Naval Range at Rossevelt Roads, Puerto Rico, is the final confirmation of the effectiveness of the highly sophisticated Naval Air Defence combination.  AMRAAM, when combined with the world beating Blue Vixen radar fitted in the FA2, gives the Royal Navy one of the most cost effective and potent fighters in the western world.    </P>

It has been proved through this series of firings against really challenging targets, that the FA2, as a relatively small aircraft, fights above its weight.
</P>

<A HREF="../latest.htm" TARGET="contents"> Back to Latest News</A>

