<head><title>Royal Navy: Worldwide: UK Clyde </title>

</head>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"  
text="#000000">



<A HREF="britain.htm" TARGET="contents"> <H4>United Kingdom</A> &#160;&#128;&#160; <A HREF="../today/bases.htm" TARGET="contents"> Naval Bases</H4></A>

<H4>HM Naval Base Clyde </H4>


<B>Naval Technical Department</B>.   The NTD in HM Naval Base Clyde is a major support engineering operation responsible to Captain Fleet Maintenance, with an outstanding record of technical achievement.  It provides all engineering support to the Fleet in the Flag Officer Scotland, Northern England and Northern Ireland (FOSNNI) area with integration between Naval, civilian and contractor staffs well established.  NTD has traditionally provided the full spectrum of nuclear submarine engineering support with the exception only of nuclear refueling.  It has now developed the skill base to support Sandown Class MCMVs and River Class PVs.  The Docks and Jetties Division of NTD is unique in that it operates the only remaining RN floating dock, AFD 60, and a nuclear qualified Shiplift.  AFD 60 and the Shiplift are crucial to support of the Independent Deterrent.</P>

<B>Engineering Works Services Departments.</B>   EWSD is responsible for the operation and maintenance of all electrical and  mechanical utility services to submarines and vessels alongside, operation of the Radioactive Effluent Disposal Facility and the Active Processing Facility.  EWSD is also the focal point for all Works and Property Management within the Base and operates a Facility Design Management Organization to ensure integrity of the Nuclear Site Safety Justification.  Arrangements are being made to integrate the Works and Property Management organization at RNAD Coulport and SSTO(N) Faslane with EWSD.  Works and Property Management at RNAD Beith, RNAD Crombie and RNSD Rosyth will be managed locally, due to their geographical remoteness from HM Naval Base Clyde.</P>

<B>HMS NEPTUNE.</B>   One of the three national Fleet Accommodation Centres, it provides a full range of personnel support services to about 3,500 HM Naval Base Clyde personnel and some 800 families.  Logistic support to all vessels based in Faslane and out stations include pay, accommodation, medical, dental, chaplaincy, welfare, recreation, discipline and security.  HMS CALEDONIA situated in the Rosyth area, is a subordinate command of HMS NEPTUNE and provides similar support to naval personnel standing by ships and submarines in refit at Rosyth.  It also provides a base for HMS SCOTIA (Naval Reserves Unit), The Royal Marine Band (Scotland), The Regional Resettlement Centre and local Sea Cadets.</P>

<B>MARINE SERVICES.</B>   Queen's Harbour Master (QHM) overseas and directs all berthing and movements in the Clyde and Rosyth Dockyard Ports, including the safe navigation of all vessels and liaison with the Clyde and Rosyth Port Authorities.  QHM is the local designated officer for the Marine Services Contract and manages the Admiralty Pilotage Service in Scotland.</p>

<B>OPERATIONS DEPARTMENT</B>.   Responsible for the efficient, timely and safe planning for an execution of all National and NATO Maritime Operations conducted within the Scottish Exercise Areas and adjacent areas as delegated to FOSNNI by CINCFLEET.  Operating from HM Naval Base Clyde Maritime Operations Centre (MOC) and the Greenock War HQ, the operations department includes a number of sub-departments, Diving, Photographic, Chart Maintenance, Communications and plans.</P>

<B>Northern Ireland Squadron.</B>   The Senior Naval Officer Northern Ireland (SNONI) is responsible for activities in Northern Ireland in support of Operations INTERKNIT, GRENADA and LIFESPAN under the delegated Operational Control (OPCON) of GOC Northern Ireland.</P>

Land Area.   FOSNNI Land Area activities include civic liaison via the Naval Regional Officers Scotland, Northern Ireland and Northern England (NROSNI and NRONE); Public relations for the Land and Sea area, Consultancy services for Works, Fire Prevention and Legal Services, and a high level of Naval representational duties.</P>

<B>Host support in HM Naval Base Clyde is provided to:</B>

<UL>
<LI>Flag Officer Sea Training (FOST)
<LI>Captain Sea and Shore Training (CSST)
<LI>Small Ships Operational Training Squadron
<LI>Royal Naval Strategic Systems School (RNSSS)
<LI>The Joint Maritime Course exercise (JMC)
<LI>Submarine Training facilities:
<LI>Submarine Command Team Trainer (SCTT)
<LI>Faslane Manoeuvring Room Trainer (FASMAT)
<LI>Nuclear Submarine Control Trainer (NUSCOT)
</UL>



<CENTER>
</P>
