<A HREF="britain.htm" TARGET="contents"> <H4>United Kingdom</A> &#160;&#128;&#160; <A HREF="../today/bases.htm" TARGET="contents"> Naval Bases</H4></A>

<H4>Royal Naval Air Station Prestwick</H4>
HMS GANNET<BR>

ARYSHIRE</P>

RNAS PRESTWICK comprises 27 acres of leased airfield site at Prestwick International Airport with instant access to  the Clyde submarine operating areas.  The base has the finest purpose built engineering facilities in naval aviation with a new twin hanger complex and squadron facilities.  Extensive refurbishment of the Operations facilities is also under way.</P>

It is a single aircraft-type station with the largest front line Sea King squadron in Royal Naval service, dedicated to the support of the UK Deterrent operations and year-round Search and Rescue with 9 Sea King aircraft.  It is one of the 3 busiest SAR units in the UK.  There are some 450 service and civilian personnel at RNAS Prestwick which also provides domestic support for 120 RAF servicemen at the nearby Scottish Air Traffic Control Centre.</P>


