<A HREF="britain.htm" TARGET="contents"> <H4>United Kingdom</A> &#160;&#128;&#160; <A HREF="../today/bases.htm" TARGET="contents"> Naval Bases</H4></A>

<H4>Royal Naval Air Station Culdrose</H4>


HMS SEAHAWK<BR>

Helston, Cornwall</P>

RNAS Culdrose and its satellite airfield, Predannack, cover 1512 acres of the Lizard Peninsular.  There are also 400 married quarters in Nearby Helston.</P>

It is the largest military helicopter base in Western Europe with seven helicopter squadrons, plus one Jetstream squadron, (in all some 80 plus aircraft and 3050 personnel including 700 civilians).  With an annual budget of some &#163;72M, Culdrose is the Typed Air Station  for Sea King ASW and AEW squadrons as well as being the busiest Search and Rescue base in England.  Basic helicopter pilot, observer and aircrew training, the Aircraft Handling School, the RN Meteorological and Oceanographic School and a large engineering school for Sea King airframes are also located there.  Many Commonwealth  and NATO Navies send their Sea King pilots to Culdrose for training.</P>

