<head><title>Royal Navy: Worldwide: UK Yeovilton </title>

</head>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"  
text="#000000">



<A HREF="britain.htm" TARGET="contents"> <H4>United Kingdom</A> &#160;&#128;&#160; <A HREF="../today/bases.htm" TARGET="contents"> Naval Bases</H4></A>

<H4>Royal Naval Air Station Yeovilton </H4>


HMS HERON<BR>

Yeovil, Somerset</P>

1,000 acres of airfield sites plus ranges and minor estate.</P>

RNAS Yeovilton is a large multi-role air station with an annual budget of some &#163;61M.  Typed Air Station for RN Sea Harriers, the RN Support Helicopter Force and Royal Naval Commando Helicopter Force.  Yeovilton operates over 80 aircraft in four different categories.</P>

<table border=2>
<tr align=top><td><B>CATEGORY</B></TD><TD><B>AIRCRAFT</B></TD><TD><B>SQUADRON/FLIGHT</B></TD> </TR>

<tr align=top><td> VSTOL</TD><TD>Sea Harrier FA2</TD><TD>800  (HMS INVINCIBLE)</TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td>&#160;</TD><TD>			Sea Harrier FA2</TD><TD>801  (HMS ILLUSTRIOUS)</TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td>&#160;</TD><TD> Harrier T4N/T8 & Sea</TD><TD>899 </TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td>&#160;</TD><TD> Harrier FA2 </TD><TD>&#160;</TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td> Turbo Prop</TD><TD>Jetstream T3</TD><TD>Heron Flight </TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td> Rotary Wing</TD><TD>Sea King HC4</TD><TD>845 </TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td>&#160;</TD><TD> Sea King HC4</TD><TD>846 </TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td>&#160;</TD><TD> Sea King HC4</TD><TD>848 </TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td>&#160;</TD><TD> Lynx AH7</TD><TD>847 </TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td>&#160;</TD><TD> Gazelle AH1 </TD><TD>&#160;</TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td> Historics</TD><TD>Swordfish</TD><TD>RNHF </TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td>&#160;</TD><TD> Firefly </TD><TD>&#160;</TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td>&#160;</TD><TD> Sea Fury </TD><TD>&#160;</TD> </TR>
<tr align=top><td>&#160;</TD><TD> Sea Hawk </TD><TD>&#160;</TD> </TR> </TABLE>

</P>

Yeovilton is manned by around 1675 service and 2000 civilian personnel including MoD employees and permanent contractors.</p>

There are 30 administered outstations, including one in Portugal, and several lodger units including FONA, DGA(N), ASE, NATO MEWSG, FAA Information Technology Programme, and, most recently, the Defence Helicopter Support Authority.</P>

Training of aircrew and engineers of resident aircraft types is also carried out at Yeovilton.  It is also the location for the RN Fighter Controller School, training ground and airborne AEW controllers.


<center>
</P>
<P>

