<html>
<head><title>Royal Navy: Worldwide: UK Portsmouth </title>

</head>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"  
text="#000000">



<A HREF="britain.htm" TARGET="contents"> <H4>United Kingdom</A> &#160;&#128;&#160; <A HREF="../today/bases.htm" TARGET="contents"> Naval Bases</H4></A>

<H4>HM Naval Base Portsmouth </H4>

<A HREF="portshis.htm" TARGET="contents">History</A>
<HR>

Portsmouth Naval base provides material, infrastructure and personnel support to meet the needs of the Fleet and other customers in peace, tension and war.  With some 60% of the operational Surface Flotilla baseported at Portsmouth, the Naval Base has combined with the Director Supplies South organization as a MOD agency to provide high quality, cost effective support to the Fleet.</P>

The Naval Base is an integral part of the Front Line and the organization is firmly focused on the waterfront.  Captain Fleet Maintenance, as the Naval base "ship agent", provides a single point of contact in fulfilling the needs of the Fleet, ensuring that the ship returns to sea in sound order ready for its operational commitments.  The Director Fleet Maintenance and Repair Organization provides engineering support for vessel maintenance and update during Upkeep Time together with dockside and Base services essential to the Naval Base task.  Captain Base Services manages the fabric of the Naval Base infrastructure to provide a safe, secure and capable facility to support the ships and lodger units which reside within the Naval base.  The Queen's Harbour Master provides  services, whilst Supply and Secretariat Department support and Naval Base Hotel services are both provided by Captain HMS NELSON.  Management services for the Naval Base are provided by the Naval Base Business Manager.  The supply to the Fleet of stores, weapons, ammunition and fuel in Portsmouth is currently managed by Director Supply (South).  Preliminary work has been put in hand by the Naval Base Commander and Director Supply (South) to review the Management organization within the Naval Base, with the declared aim of moving to a fully integrated organization at Portsmouth under a single head.</P>

The taut operational Programme and the pace of change demand a responsive, capable and flexible support organization at the waterfront, and pressures on the defence budget demand ever increasing efficiency.  Portsmouth Naval Base takes pride in the service it offers, but recognizes the need to increase efficiency and value for money by improving business practices and developing skilled, unified teams which will help to build a shared sense of purpose.  NBC Portsmouth is intent on generating an integrated Naval Base that will deliver the best possible output to the Fleet in terms of quality, timeliness and cost.


<center>
</P>
<P>

<HR WIDTH="50%">



<A TARGET="_parent" HREF="../index.htm">Home Page</A>





