<head><title>Royal Navy: Worldwide: UK Plymouth </title>

</head>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"  
text="#000000">




<A HREF="britain.htm" TARGET="contents"> <H4>United Kingdom</H4></A>

<A HREF="plymouth.htm" TARGET="contents"> <H4>HM Naval Base, Plymouth </H4></A>




<H4>Flag Officer Sea Training</H4>

<P> Over the past 36 years Flag Officer Sea Training - or FOST as he is
inevitably called - and his staff, based in Portland, have provided a centre of
excellence for what is arguably the most effective and demanding operational sea
training package available anywhere in the world.  A new era began on 21 July
1995, however, when, as part of the rationalisation of Naval assets, FOST sailed
out of East Ship Channel at Portland for the last time in HMS ARGYLL and moved
down the coast to Plymouth.  However, while the location may have changed,
offering new challenges, FOST's basic philosophy and impact remains the same.</P>
<P>The last three years, in particular, have seen a marked increase in the
number of countries which have sent ships to FOST for training.  Apart from well
established customers such as  the Netherlands, Germany and Belgium, more
recently ships have undergone training from Portugal, Greece, Italy, Spain,
Pakistan, Brazil and Turkey.</p>


</P>
<P>

<center>

