<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Publisher's Note </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="../HomePage.html"><IMG SRC="../hci/HdrBtn1Home.gif"
BORDER="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="113" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></A><A HREF="Archives.html"><IMG SRC=
"../hci/HdrBtn2Arch.gif" BORDER="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="91" HEIGHT="44"
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></A><A HREF="../search/wais.cgi"><IMG SRC="../hci/HdrBtn3Sear.gif"
BORDER="0" ALT="search" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="91" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></A><A HREF="../brochure/Help.html"><IMG SRC="../hci/HdrBtn4Help.gif"
BORDER="0" ALT="Help" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="91" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></A><A HREF="1296.Contents.html"><IMG SRC="../hci/HdrBtn5Contents.gif"
BORDER="0" ALT="Contents" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="83" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></A> <BR>
<A HREF="1296.Editorial.html"><IMG SRC="../hci/HdrBtnBck.gif" BORDER="0"
ALT="Previous" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="67" HEIGHT="40" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></A><IMG SRC=
"../hci/H3Publish.gif" BORDER="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="363" HEIGHT="40"
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><A HREF="1296.GuestEditorial.html"><IMG SRC="../hci/HdrBtnNxt.gif"
BORDER="0" ALT="Next" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="40" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></A> </CENTER>
<P><B><IMG SRC="../pictures/publisher.gif" BORDER="0" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=
"93" HEIGHT="122" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Bad Karma?<BR>
</FONT SIZE> <FONT size=+1></B>Negative Feelings Aren't Always Bad;<BR>
They Can Awaken and Unite a Community<BR>
<B></FONT></B><BR>
<B><I>By Linda A. Dickerson - Publisher <BR clear=all></I></B><HR>The number-crunchers
will argue about exactness. The researchers will challenge validity. The
cynics will cast their normal aspersions. But the facts will ultimately
speak for themselves. This calendar year, the region is on a path that will
fall well short of the goal to create 100,000 new jobs by the year 2000.
<BR>
<BR>
Throughout 1995, this region added jobs more rapidly than the state. However
while the state and national economies grew, the region actually lost thousands
of jobs this past summer.<BR>
<BR>
Job creation is the most accurate barometer of an economy's vitality  and
is essential to prosperity. Therefore, I'm a pragmatist - not a soothsayer
of doom and gloom - when I say the Pittsburgh economy continues to face
serious challenges. This region cannot afford to maintain the status quo.
Decision makers must subrogate self interest and coalesce around a common
purpose.<BR>
<BR>
Does this news mean that the battle is lost, that we can't achieve our goal?
Most emphatically not. Does focusing attention on the shortcomings exposed
in the job reports create negative karma which holds back the region? I
don't see it that way. Negative karma can be a constructive force, awakening
a community's understanding of harsh realities in an intensely competitive
world.<BR>
 <BR>
But economic growth has yet to become the maypole around which this area's
energies are wrapped. That's in spite of valiant effort from hundreds of
volunteers in The Working Together Consortium, the  mechanism designed to
bring decision-makers together toward a common future. Extraordin-arily
well-conceived, the consortium breaks the anti-cooperative paradigm that
dominated the region for years. The bad news is, they're struggling.<BR>
<BR>
Yet in each of 10 priority areas, the consortium recounts solid progress.
 At the same time, we hear others declaring us to be among the 10 best cities
to balance work and family, among the 10 best large citiesfor small business
and the city with the third highest rate in business incorporations through
the first half of 1996. That's good news.<BR>
<BR>
This region seems to be confused about the &quot;proper&quot; psychological
approach to transforming its economy. Rather than running from the bad news
and chastising people for not thinking positively, I believe we need to
combine a healthy dose of realism to point out our weak spots with an unapologetic
celebration of the successes mentioned above to invigorate our spirit and
to build the positive momentum we need to carry us to our goal.<BR>
<HR><A HREF="../HomePage.html"><IMG SRC="../hci/HdrBtn1Home.gif" BORDER=
"0" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="113" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></A><A HREF="Archives.html"><IMG SRC=
"../hci/HdrBtn2Arch.gif" BORDER="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="91" HEIGHT="44"
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></A><A HREF="../search/wais.cgi"><IMG SRC="../hci/HdrBtn3Sear.gif"
BORDER="0" ALT="search" ALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="91" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></A><A HREF="../brochure/Help.html"><IMG SRC="../hci/HdrBtn4Help.gif"
